    "context": "Hong Kong taxis are colour-coded: red for urban areas, green for the New Territories, blue for Lantau. Red taxis are the most common. Drivers appreciate it if you know your destination and can give cross-street landmarks. Always have the Chinese characters for your destination ready.",
    "cultural_note": "Hong Kong taxis are colour-coded: red urban taxis can roam almost the whole territory; green taxis are confined to the New Territories; blue taxis serve Lantau only. A green cab cannot legally pick up a passenger in Central, which is why drivers sometimes refuse trips that strand them outside their zone. On cross-harbour trips you pay the tunnel toll both ways, unless you find a cab at a cross-harbour rank already heading home.",
